    "rationale": "Credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors at MRL 5 for Class III VAD device. Seven factors assessed with achieved levels uniformly below required levels; six factors not assessed due to resource and data constraints. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed over inlet boundary conditions and is discussed extensively in the assessment narrative. The team notes that aleatory uncertainty from red blood cell fragility variability, manufacturing tolerance scatter, and PIV measurement variability is acknowledged in prose throughout the report; however, formal UQ artifact linkage to individual validation result nodes was not completed within the assessment timeline. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for the intended submission given the low assurance level designation, with the understanding that the unlinked aleatory uncertainty sources represent open items for follow-on assessment cycles.",
